$version Generated by tool/generate_bldc_fixtures.dart $end
$comment BLDC spin-up hero demo — idle -> spin-up to ~2200 RPM -> cruise -> decel -> low idle, 2 pole-pairs, 2 s @ 800 Hz. Rotor angle, 3-phase sinusoidal drive, Hall sensors, 6-step commutation, and DC-bus current all move together. Built to drive the Pro BLDC Rive widget for the beta demo recording. $end
$date 2026-06-20 $end
$timescale 1ns $end
$scope module top $end
$scope module motor $end
$var wire 1 ! sample_clk $end
$var wire 16 " rpm $end
$var wire 16 # mech_angle $end
$var wire 16 $ elec_angle $end
$var wire 10 % throttle $end
$var wire 16 & phase_u $end
$var wire 16 ' phase_v $end
$var wire 16 ( phase_w $end
$var wire 1 ) hall_u $end
$var wire 1 * hall_v $end
$var wire 1 + hall_w $end
$var wire 3 , comm_state $end
$var wire 1 - direction $end
$var wire 16 . bus_current $end
$upscope $end
$upscope $end
$enddefinitions $end
